        "creation_date": 1349317495,
        "body": "<p>No there is not a builtin method to do this. <\/p>\n\n<p>But there are other means, some comes into thoughts :<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Send the File object to a remote java object via RMI using a tool like <a href=\"http://openhms.sourceforge.net/rmiio/\" rel=\"nofollow\">RMIIO<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Zip the folder and upload it to a remote host using HTTP or FTP<\/li>\n<li>Or you can even upload the zipped folder to a raw socket port<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
